<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Described from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="páramos">paramos</normalizedToken>
of Costa Rica, and mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse (1994)</bibRefCitation>
to also occur in alpine pastures of Guatemala and Mexico, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been included in checklists for Colombia (
<bibRefCitation author="Giraldo-Canas, D" editor="Bernal, R" journalOrPublisher="2). Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota D. C." pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="2127 - 2205" refId="B10" refString="Giraldo-Canas, D, Londono, X, Clark, LG, 2016. Poaceae. In: Bernal, R, Gradstein, SR, Celis, M, Eds., Catalogo de plantas y liquenes de Colombia (Vol. 2). Instituto de Ciencias Naturales, Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota D.C.: 2127 - 2205" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Catalogo de plantas y liquenes de Colombia (Vol." year="2016">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Giraldo-Cañas">Giraldo-Canas</normalizedToken>
et al. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) and Venezuela (
<bibRefCitation author="Hokche, O" journalOrPublisher="Fundacion Instituto Botanico de Venezuela, Caracas" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" refId="B16" refString="Hokche, O, Berry, PE, Huber, O [Eds], 2008. Nuevo Catalogo de la Flora Vascular de Venezuela. Fundacion Instituto Botanico de Venezuela, Caracas" title="Nuevo Catalogo de la Flora Vascular de Venezuela." year="2008">Hokche et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
). However, there is a lack of consensus on the identity of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and how to differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l., with all type material of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its synonyms out on loan at the time of writing this publication to help clarify this. The principal discrepancy refers to the form of the leaf blades, with the protologue and 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl (1980)</bibRefCitation>
mentioning filiform flat or folded leaf blades, while 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Morales-Quiros, JF" editor="Hammel, BE" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93 (3)" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="598 - 821" refId="B22" refString="Morales-Quiros, JF, 2003. Poaceae. In: Hammel, BE, Grayum, MH, Herrera-Mora, C, Zamora-Villalobos, N, Eds., Manual of Plants of Costa Rica. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93(3): 598 - 821" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Manual of Plants of Costa Rica." year="2003">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morales-Quirós">Morales-Quiros</normalizedToken>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
state the blades to be involute and narrow, 0.2-1 mm in diameter as rolled, and rarely the cauline leaf blades being flat, and use this character to differentiate it from the usually flat bladed 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This may relate to the species 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. arcta" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="arcta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. arcta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. vesca" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="vesca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. vesca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, described from Guatemala and considered synonyms of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, with the protologues mentioning leaf blades being firm, folded and involute, curved, in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. arcta" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="arcta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. arcta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or flat, filiform, or involute and straight in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. vesca" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="vesca">A. vesca</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Agrostis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Agrostis perennans" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perennans">Agrostis perennans</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, in its broad sense, can also have involute or filiform leaf blades based on species currently considered synonyms of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, e.g. 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. aberrans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. aberrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Steud., 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. kufium" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="kufium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. kufium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Speg., 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. tenuifolia subsp. var. var. fretensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="variety" species="tenuifolia" subSpecies="var." variety="fretensis">A. tenuifolia M. Bieb. var. fretensis</taxonomicName>
Hook. f., 
<taxonomicName authority="P.Beauv., 1812" authorityName="Kunth" authorityYear="1816" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Vilfa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vilfa elegans" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Vilfa elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
While all literature (
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Morales-Quiros, JF" editor="Hammel, BE" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93 (3)" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="598 - 821" refId="B22" refString="Morales-Quiros, JF, 2003. Poaceae. In: Hammel, BE, Grayum, MH, Herrera-Mora, C, Zamora-Villalobos, N, Eds., Manual of Plants of Costa Rica. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93(3): 598 - 821" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Manual of Plants of Costa Rica." year="2003">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morales-Quirós">Morales-Quiros</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) also differentiates 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by stating there is a lack of conspicuous basal foliage in the former, this may not be a good differentiating character as 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
usually has blades concentrated at the base of the plant when it is young, and only in subsequent flowering seasons it begins to elongate and lose its basal foliage. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl (1980)</bibRefCitation>
also mentions that paleas are minute in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
paleas are absent, but this character appears to be too variable to be useful. Discrepancy in spikelet size is also apparent, with the 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
protologue stating 1.75 mm long and the 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. vesca" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="vesca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. vesca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
protologue stating 1.6-1.8 mm long, while all other publications describing the species (
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Burger, WC" journalOrPublisher="Fieldiana Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="1 - 608" refId="B27" refString="Pohl, RW, 1980. Family 15. Gramineae. In: Burger, WC, Ed., Flora Costaricensis. Fieldiana Botany 4: 1 - 608" title="Family 15. Gramineae." volume="4" volumeTitle="Flora Costaricensis." year="1980">Pohl 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pohl, RW" editor="Davidse, G" journalOrPublisher="Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="237 - 240" refId="B28" refString="Pohl, RW, Davidse, G, 1994. 46. Agrostis L. In: Davidse, G, Sousa, M, Sanchez, MS, Chater, AO, Eds., Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6). Alismataceae a Cyperaceae. Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, Mexico: 237 - 240" title="46. Agrostis L." volumeTitle="Flora Mesoamericana (Vol 6)." year="1994">Pohl and Davidse 1994</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Morales-Quiros, JF" editor="Hammel, BE" journalOrPublisher="Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93 (3)" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="598 - 821" refId="B22" refString="Morales-Quiros, JF, 2003. Poaceae. In: Hammel, BE, Grayum, MH, Herrera-Mora, C, Zamora-Villalobos, N, Eds., Manual of Plants of Costa Rica. Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 93(3): 598 - 821" title="Poaceae." volumeTitle="Manual of Plants of Costa Rica." year="2003">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Morales-Quirós">Morales-Quiros</normalizedToken>
2003
</bibRefCitation>
) state 2-2.1 mm or 2-2.8 mm long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
We here tentatively differentiate the two species by 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having leaf blades filiform, 0.2-1 mm wide when opened out, thin and flaccid, leaves mainly basal at maturity, and plants generally smaller with culms to 40 cm tall and panicles to 12 cm long and 6 cm wide (vs. leaf blades flat or conduplicate, (1-)1.5-6 mm wide when opened out, rarely involute in the basal leaves, usually thickened at the margins and keel, firm, leaves mainly basal early in the flowering season but tending to become mostly cauline with maturity, and plants generally larger, with culms to 100 cm tall and panicles often larger, to 22 cm long and 11 cm wide in 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. perennans" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="perennans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. perennans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s.l.). No specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that fit this delineation have been found at US from either Colombia or Venezuela. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. turrialbae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="turrialbae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A. turrialbae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be better included among the broad 
